        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COST</span>&nbsp; How much does a hot water cylinder cost in Liverpool?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A vented indirect cylinder supply and fit starts from £600. An unvented cylinder starts from £900. Immersion heater replacement from £150. Prices depend on cylinder capacity, type and access. We provide a free fixed-price quote after a site visit.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">TYPES</span>&nbsp; What is the difference between vented and unvented cylinders?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A vented cylinder is fed from a cold water tank in the loft at low pressure. Common in Liverpool's older properties. An unvented cylinder is fed directly from the mains, delivering hot water at mains pressure. Better shower performance and no loft tank needed. Unvented must be installed by a G3 qualified engineer.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COMBI</span>&nbsp; Should I get a cylinder or a combi boiler?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A combi boiler heats water on demand and requires no cylinder. Ideal for smaller Liverpool properties with one bathroom. Larger properties with multiple bathrooms or higher hot water demand benefit from a system boiler with an unvented cylinder, which delivers mains-pressure hot water to multiple outlets simultaneously without running out. We advise at the free survey.</p></div></details>
